Class DeleteRecordController

  • java.lang.Object
    • controllers.DeleteRecordController
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    javafx.fxml.Initializable
    public class DeleteRecordController
extends java.lang.Object
implements javafx.fxml.Initializable
    This class is the controller of DeleteRecordMenu.fxml. The class displays the data of the Customer Record to be deleted as well as a table view with all related Appointments.
    Since:
    2021-12-13

      • onActionDeleteAppt

        public void onActionDeleteAppt​(javafx.event.ActionEvent event)
        This method is called when the "Delete Appointment" button is clicked. This method confirms the users decision and DELETES the appointment from the database and updates the repository and tableview.

        RUNTIME ERROR: If the user does not have an appointment selected or if the DELETE from the database fails, an error message will appear.

        Parameters:
        event - is not used

      • fillApptTableView

        public void fillApptTableView​(javafx.collections.ObservableList<Appointment> apptList)
        This method is used by other methods within the class. This method will populate the table view with all Appointments passed in as a parameter.
        Parameters:
        apptList - contains all Appointments to be displayed in the table view

      • onActionCancelButton

        public void onActionCancelButton​(javafx.event.ActionEvent event)
                          throws java.io.IOException
        This method is called when the "Cancel" button is clicked. This method sends the user to RecordMenu.fxml without Updating the Customer Record.
        Parameters:
        event - high-level event used to set the Stage
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - required by the FXMLLoader.load() function

      • onActionRemoveButton

        public void onActionRemoveButton​(javafx.event.ActionEvent event)
                          throws java.io.IOException
        This method is called when the "Delete Record" button is clicked. This method confirms the users decision and DELETES the Customer Record from the database and Returns to the Record Menu.

        RUNTIME ERROR: Should the DELETE from the database fail, an error message will appear.

        Parameters:
        event - high-level event used to set the Stage
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - required by the FXMLLoader.load() function
